Notebook[{

Cell["P3HT / O-IDTBR Charge-Transfer Exciton Model", "Title"],

Cell["Companion code for: Jindal, Janik & Milner, \"First-Principles Modeling of Interfacial Charge Transfer Exciton States in Organic Solar Cells\" (JCTC).", "Subtitle"],

Cell["Overview", "Section"],

Cell["This notebook orchestrates the full calculation of charge-transfer (CT) exciton energies at a P3HT / O-IDTBR donor-acceptor interface, using a tight-binding model parameterized from DFT and applied to close-contact geometries taken from a molecular dynamics trajectory.

The total CT exciton energy is E_CT = E_K + E_C + E_P, i.e. the one-body kinetic energy of the delocalized electron and hole (E_K), the electron-hole Coulomb interaction (E_C), and the dielectric polarization stabilization (E_P) (Eq. 2 and Eq. 12 of the paper).

Each step below loads one commented Wolfram Language module from the src/ directory. Evaluate the cells in order. Required input data must be present in data/ (see DATA_MANIFEST.md).", "Text"],

Cell["How to run", "Section"],

Cell["1. Place the input data files in the data/ directory (see DATA_MANIFEST.md).
2. Evaluate the 'Setup' cell to set the working directory to this notebook's folder.
3. Evaluate each module cell in order (00 through 09). The final module, 09, produces the CT exciton energies and the decomposition used for Figures 8-13 and Table 3.
Note: module 09 minimizes the exciton energy for all 237 contacts and may take several minutes.", "Text"],

Cell["Setup", "Section"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"SetDirectory", "[", "NotebookDirectory", "[", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"rootDir", " ", "=", " ", "NotebookDirectory", "[", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"dataDir", " ", "=", " ", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"data\"", "}", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"resultsDir", " ", "=", " ", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"results\"", "}", "]"}]], "Input"]
}, Open]],

Cell["Workflow modules (evaluate in order)", "Section"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Configuration & physical constants (paths, eps, eFac, fac).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"00_config.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Import the MD frame (npt.gro): box, P3HT & IDTBR atoms.", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"01_import_configuration.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Ring centres and the 237 BT-thiophene close contacts.", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"02_ring_centers_close_contacts.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Smeared (Gaussian) 14x14 Coulomb kernel (Eq. 6-7).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"03_coulomb_interaction_matrix.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Interchain hopping t_ab from the ML model (Fig. 6).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"04_interchain_hopping_ML.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Intrachain hopping from DFT dimer energies (Figs. 4-5).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"05_intrachain_hopping_DFT.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Assemble onsite, hopping & Coulomb parameters (Tables 1-2).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"06_gather_parameters.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Polaron states as initial guesses for the CT minimization.", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"07_polaron_initial_condition.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["14x14 CT-exciton tight-binding Hamiltonian (Eq. 4).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"08_hamiltonian_matrix.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"],
Cell["Total E_CT = E_K + E_C + E_P (Eq. 12), decomposition & analysis (Figs. 8-13, Table 3).", "Text"],
Cell[BoxData[RowBox[{"Get", "[", "FileNameJoin", "[", "{", "rootDir", ",", " ", "\"src\"", ",", " ", "\"09_ct_exciton_energy_analysis.wl\"", "}", "]", "]"}]], "Input"]
}, Open]],

Cell["Key outputs", "Section"],

Cell["After running all modules the following symbols hold the main results:
  ExcitonEnergies2  - CT exciton energy for each contact (Fig. 9)
  ExcitonEnergies3  - IDTBR-localized exciton energy for each contact (Fig. 8)
  results           - per-contact {E_CT, E_C+E_P, E_K, E_C, E_P, E_Ke, E_Kh, psiE, psiH}
  keepIdx / RemoveIds - main population vs. outlier indices (Table 3)
  table3Main / table3Outliers - mean Coulomb / polarization energies (Table 3)
  lm2 / residuals2   - refined E_CT vs E_1b linear fit (Fig. 11)", "Text"]

},
 WindowSize->{900, 800},
